OL,4,Cyears due to discovery of radioactive
OL,5,Cgas
OL,7,FRadon gas is formed by the radioactive
OL,8,Fdecay of small amounts of uranium that
OL,9,Foccur naturally in all rocks and
OL,10,Fsoils. However, in high levels,
OL,11,Fexposure to the gas can lead to an
OL,12,Fincreased risk of lung cancer.
OL,14,FThe gas is responsible for around
OL,15,F1,000 lung cancer deaths a year and is
OL,16,Fthought to occur more often in areas
OL,17,Fwith high concentrations of granite,
OL,18,Fsuch as Dartmoor.
