OL,5,Cgas
OL,7,FWhile it was first detected in 2023
OL,8,Fleading to the initial evacuation, the
OL,9,FMoJ hoped it had been alleviated by
OL,10,F"purging" the gas from the prison
OL,11,Fleading to some prisoners returning to
OL,12,Fthe site the following year. This was
OL,13,Fquickly reversed in July, a decision
OL,14,Fthat the POA backed at the time as the
OL,15,Fcorrect decision".
OL,17,FSpeaking at the time of the second
OL,18,Fevacuation, Steve Gillan, POA general
OL,19,Fsecretary, said the closure had "come
OL,20,Fat the worst possible time with
OL,21,Fovercrowding".
