OL,3,CPrison to be shut for a further three
OL,4,Cyears due to discovery of radioactive
OL,5,Cgas
OL,7,FSome 1,700 inmates were freed after
OL,8,Fserving 40% of their sentence, rather
OL,9,Fthan the usual 50% in September 2024.
OL,11,FA further 1,100 prisoners were
OL,12,Freleased in October, bringing the
OL,13,Fprison population down to around
OL,14,F86,000.
OL,16,FThe government set limits on who could
OL,17,Fbe freed, with the early release
OL,18,Fscheme excluding those behind bars who
OL,19,Fhave been convicted of sex offences,
OL,20,Fterrorism, domestic abuse or some
OL,21,Fviolent offences.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
